{
  "texts": [
    "It is evident from the results that the MediaPipe framework tends to outperform when compared to Kinect-based skeleton tracking in all possible joint movements.",
    "The result shows that the robot can mimic a human pose in real time, regardless of surrounding luminescence or the presence of an unknown user in the frame.",
    "Moreover, the results of the comparison are demonstrated for both static and dynamic conditions of human body movement.",
    "Further, more complex robot configurations can also be considered for the development of human-robot interactions.",
    "The proposed frameworks are efficient and produce less error."
  ]
}